WorkItem.Description:
This is a feature request.

I'd like to have a shorthand for constructing a hash with property-names identical to local variable-names, as this is a common task - example with current syntax:

```
interface User { name: string }

interface LoginEvent { user: User }

function onLogin(event: LoginEvent) {
	// ...
}

var user = { name: "John" };

onLogin({user: user});
```

I'd like to be able to shorten the last line to:

```
onLogin({user});
```

This would compile into the same code, with the property-name assumed to be `user`, same as the local variable, since nothing else was specified.
